  1â†’//! Concolic execution loop: worklist-driven path exploration with Z3 solving.
  2â†’//!
  3â†’//! The orchestrator drives the concolic testing cycle:
  4â†’//! 1. Seed the worklist with initial inputs
  5â†’//! 2. Execute a function concretely via a frontend subprocess
  6â†’//! 3. Collect branch constraints from the execution trace
  7â†’//! 4. Negate each branch constraint and solve with Z3 for new inputs
  8â†’//! 5. Add solved inputs to the worklist; repeat until done
  9â†’//!
 10â†’//! Inputs from Z3 are prioritized over fuzzed or seed inputs so that the
 11â†’//! solver-guided exploration is always tried first.
 12â†’
